method_1 = Run warm water in the tub (not hot), seat your baby in the tub with their upper body above water level, then add drops of rubbing alcohol to the bath water.
)item_2 = Dry-weight cardboard box
method_2 = Place dry cardboard boxes around your child's room, then open windows and doors to let cool air flow through them so it circulates and evaporates body heat before the child can sweat it out
urgent_advice = The most important thing you must know: NEVER attempt any of these methods unless temperatures are above 104°F!

test_method_1 = Look for a distinct cap and stem (many poisonous mushrooms have features that are very similar to edible varieties, so this can quickly narrow down the options!);
test_method_2 = If you're unsure, search online, you can identify them by taking pictures and searching the web!;
test_method_3 = If you're really uncertain, do the 'duck test' (drop the mushroom in water, if it floats, it's safe to eat!');
safety_warning = Many people die from eating wild mushrooms every year - for that reason, it's extremely important to only eat them when you've identified the species yourself!;
recommendation = When in doubt, don't eat them, and if you find yourself unsure about something, just plug in the word 'pictures' and hit search.
